  "description": "A first-year course introducing computer architecture from the gate level up to the operating system. Part I covers digital logic (Boole algebra, combinational and sequential circuits), data representations (fixed-point, floating-point), and the computer's memory system. Part II covers CPU performance techniques (pipeline, branch prediction, speculative execution), multiprocessor systems, I/O and interrupts, and OS internals (process management, memory management, IPC, program linking).",
